body:
There was once a woman who was very, very cheerful, though she had little to make her so;
 for she was old, and poor, and lonely. She lived in a little bit of a cottage and earned a scant living by running errands for her neighbours, getting a bite here, a sup there, as reward for her services.
 So she made shift to get on, and always looked as spry and cheery as if she had not a want in the world.
